# Keep Docs in Sync

When you change code, update the matching documentation in the same change. If the doc does not exist yet, create it.

## Schema changes

Applies to: `app/models/`, `app/schemas/`, `migrations/`

→ Update `docs/SCHEMA.md` with new/changed tables, columns, types, and constraints.

## Architecture changes

Applies to: providers, routes, jobs, webhooks, CLI, config, normalizers, `app/explore.py`

→ Update `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`. Also update `README.md` if user-facing commands or setup steps change.

## ML pipeline changes

Applies to: `hr_selection/` (features, priors, models, training, evaluation, synthetic data, config)

→ Update `docs/ML_SYSTEM.md`.

## Provider normalizer changes

Applies to: `app/providers/*/normalizer.py`

→ Update that provider's `MAPPING.md` with field-level mapping changes.

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] Every new table or column is reflected in `docs/SCHEMA.md`
- [ ] Every new provider, route, or job is reflected in `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- [ ] Every new ML feature, model, or dataset is reflected in `docs/ML_SYSTEM.md`
- [ ] Provider field mappings are reflected in the relevant `MAPPING.md`
